==English==

{{rank|bright|scarcely|Paris|733|expression|Duke|battle|bound}}

===Etymology===
Ex is Latin for out. 

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}} 
# A particular way of [[phrase|phrasing]] an idea.
# A [[colloquialism]] or [[idiom]].
#: ''The '''expression''' "break a leg!" should not be taken literally.''
# A [[facial]] [[appearance]] usually associated with an [[emotion]], (though looking blank and eavesdropping also are expressions).
# (''Math'') A set of [[symbols]] denoting values and operations performed on them.
# (''Biology'') The process of translating a [[gene]] into a [[protein]].
# (''Programming'') A piece of code in a [[high-level language]] that returns a value.

